title: Cowdenbeath 2-2 Stenhousemuir: Match Report
text:
Cowdenbeath 2-2 Stenhousemuir: Match Report 17 Oct 2015 16:32:00 
comments Small makes big impression on Stenhousemuir debutLewis Small scored on his debut to rescue a point for Stenhousemuir in their dramatic 2-2 draw with Cowdenbeath.The hosts broke the deadlock in the 24th minute when Donaldson headed into the back of Jamie Barclay's net from the middle of the area.And the Blue Brazil looked on course to record just their third win of the season when Greig Spence fired into the bottom corner to make it 2-0 in the 70th minute.But Colin McMenamin's 87th-minute header saw Stenhousemuir reduce the deficit to one goal, before substitute Small earned his side a share of the spoils in the 90th minute.
